───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
                                So true is dead.
                                   For real.

This is a call to all artists. This is directed towards what's left of true,
all the group leaders out there, and all the good artists still drawing but
contributing nothing to the scene or competition.

Now that you're groupless, you're going to need another group (wait, this isn't
what you think it's going to be). And I'm saying, the scene needs you. Don't
join Mimic, and don't join CMM. Join one of the smaller, young groups that's
not run by an established scene figure. Or, start your own group. Do something,
because the scene needs help. The scene today is 2 strong groups, and about
5 shitty ones. Do something about this. Seeing as how mimic doesn't dare
to compete with the millionares, there isn't any competition anymore. You guys
can change this. Start a new group, or join an existing group. Use your name
recognition to build status for a group like hazmat, or secular. There's a ton
of talent out there.
In fact... i could create a fantasy group right now from people who are
groupless or in a group that sucks, or never releases (galza)

Mydknight, otium man, iron lung, dr. shizuma, haji, spinsane, knocturnal,
aCk, holocaust, cat-dog, and about 10 others i cant remember right now.

That group right there would blow away cmm or mimic, hands down.

You can't continue to rely on established group leaders to start groups
and compete. We're tired of it (me, cain, black jack, necromancer, etc).

The scene is not dead, it's just that the talent is spread out and lazy.

Where are the up and coming superstars? Somebody do something, and make
a name for yourself. Quit your comfortable "artist" position in mimic,
or wherever you are, and go out on a limb. Do something innovative, or
creative.

Do something for your scene.

-sargon
